defs.docs: webpki: Web PKI X.509 Certificate Validation.

attributes.value:
forbid(anonymous_parameters, box_pointers, missing_copy_implementations,
         missing_docs, trivial_casts, trivial_numeric_casts, unsafe_code,

defs.name: DNSName
defs.docs:
A DNS Name suitable for use in the TLS Server Name Indication (SNI)
 extension and/or for use as the reference hostname for which to verify a
 certificate.

defs.name: as_ref
defs.docs: Returns a `DNSNameRef` that refers to this `DNSName`.

defs.name: DNSNameRef
defs.docs:
A reference to a DNS Name suitable for use in the TLS Server Name Indication
 (SNI) extension and/or for use as the reference hostname for which to verify
 a certificate.

defs.name: try_from_ascii
defs.docs:
Constructs a `DNSNameRef` from the given input if the input is a
 syntactically-valid DNS name.

defs.name: try_from_ascii_str

Constructs a `DNSNameRef` from the given input if the input is a
 syntactically-valid DNS name.

defs.docs: Constructs a `DNSName` from this `DNSNameRef`

defs.name: Time
defs.docs: The time type.

defs.name: try_from
defs.docs: Create a `webpki::Time` from a `std::time::SystemTime`.

defs.name: from_seconds_since_unix_epoch
defs.docs: Create a `webpki::Time` from a unix timestamp.

defs.name: BadDER
defs.docs: The encoding of some ASN.1 DER-encoded item is invalid.

defs.name: BadDERTime
defs.docs: The encoding of an ASN.1 DER-encoded time is invalid.

defs.name: CAUsedAsEndEntity
defs.docs: A CA certificate is veing used as an end-entity certificate.

defs.name: CertExpired
defs.docs:
The certificate is expired; i.e. the time it is being validated for is
 later than the certificate's notAfter time.

defs.name: CertNotValidForName
defs.docs: The certificate is not valid for the name it is being validated for.

defs.name: CertNotValidYet
defs.docs:
The certificate is not valid yet; i.e. the time it is being validated
 for is earlier than the certificate's notBefore time.

defs.name: EndEntityUsedAsCA
defs.docs: An end-entity certificate is being used as a CA certificate.

defs.name: ExtensionValueInvalid
defs.docs: An X.509 extension is invalid.

defs.name: InvalidCertValidity
defs.docs:
The certificate validity period (notBefore, notAfter) is invalid; e.g.
 the notAfter time is earlier than the notBefore time.

defs.name: InvalidSignatureForPublicKey
defs.docs: The signature is invalid for the given public key.

defs.name: NameConstraintViolation
defs.docs: The certificate violates one or more name constraints.

defs.name: PathLenConstraintViolated
defs.docs: The certificate violates one or more path length constraints.

defs.name: SignatureAlgorithmMismatch
defs.docs:
The algorithm in the TBSCertificate "signature" field of a certificate
 does not match the algorithm in the signature of the certificate.

defs.name: RequiredEKUNotFound
defs.docs:
The certificate is not valid for the Extended Key Usage for which it is
 being validated.

defs.name: UnknownIssuer
defs.docs: A valid issuer for the certificate could not be found.

defs.name: UnsupportedCertVersion
defs.docs: The certificate is not a v3 X.509 certificate.

defs.name: UnsupportedCriticalExtension
defs.docs: The certificate contains an unsupported critical extension.

defs.name: UnsupportedSignatureAlgorithmForPublicKey
defs.docs:
The signature's algorithm does not match the algorithm of the public
 key it is being validated for. This may be because the public key
 algorithm's OID isn't recognized (e.g. DSA), or the public key
 algorithm's parameters don't match the supported parameters for that
 algorithm (e.g. ECC keys for unsupported curves), or the public key
 algorithm and the signature algorithm simply don't match (e.g.
 verifying an RSA signature with an ECC public key).

defs.name: UnsupportedSignatureAlgorithm
defs.docs:
The signature algorithm for a signature is not in the set of supported
 signature algorithms given.

defs.name: Error
defs.value: Error::{BadDER, BadDERTime, CAUsedAsEndEntity, CertExpired, CertNotValidForName, CertNotValidYet, EndEntityUsedAsCA, ExtensionValueInvalid, InvalidCertValidity, InvalidSignatureForPublicKey, NameConstraintViolation, PathLenConstraintViolated, SignatureAlgorithmMismatch, RequiredEKUNotFound, UnknownIssuer, UnsupportedCertVersion, UnsupportedCriticalExtension, UnsupportedSignatureAlgorithmForPublicKey, UnsupportedSignatureAlgorithm}
defs.docs: An error that occurs during certificate validation or name validation.

defs.name: trust_anchor_util
defs.docs: Utilities for efficiently embedding trust anchors in programs.

defs.name: cert_der_as_trust_anchor
defs.docs:
Interprets the given DER-encoded certificate as a `TrustAnchor`. The
 certificate is not validated. In particular, there is no check that the
 certificate is self-signed or even that the certificate has the cA basic
 constraint.

defs.name: generate_code_for_trust_anchors
defs.docs:
Generates code for hard-coding the given trust anchors into a program. This
 is designed to be used in a build script. `name` is the name of the public
 static variable that will contain the TrustAnchor array.

defs.name: EndEntityCert
defs.docs: An end-entity certificate.

defs.name: from
defs.docs:
Parse the ASN.1 DER-encoded X.509 encoding of the certificate
 `cert_der`.

defs.name: verify_is_valid_tls_server_cert
defs.value: fn (&self, supported_sig_algs: &[&SignatureAlgorithm], &TLSServerTrustAnchors(trust_anchors): &TLSServerTrustAnchors, intermediate_certs: &[untrusted::Input], time: Time) -> Result<(), Error>
defs.docs:
Verifies that the end-entity certificate is valid for use by a TLS
 server.

defs.name: verify_is_valid_tls_client_cert
defs.value: fn (&self, supported_sig_algs: &[&SignatureAlgorithm], &TLSClientTrustAnchors(trust_anchors): &TLSClientTrustAnchors, intermediate_certs: &[untrusted::Input], time: Time) -> Result<(), Error>
defs.docs:
Verifies that the end-entity certificate is valid for use by a TLS
 client.

defs.name: verify_is_valid_for_dns_name
defs.docs: Verifies that the certificate is valid for the given DNS host name.

defs.name: verify_is_valid_for_at_least_one_dns_name
defs.value: fn <'names, Names> (&self, dns_names: Names) -> Result<std::vec::Vec<DNSNameRef<'names>>, Error>
defs.docs:
Verifies that the certificate is valid for at least one of the given DNS
 host names.

defs.name: verify_signature
defs.value: fn (&self, signature_alg: &SignatureAlgorithm, msg: untrusted::Input, signature: untrusted::Input) -> Result<(), Error>
defs.docs:
Verifies the signature `signature` of message `msg` using the
 certificate's public key.

defs.name: TrustAnchor
defs.docs: A trust anchor (a.k.a. root CA).

defs.name: subject

defs.name: spki
defs.docs: The value of the `subjectPublicKeyInfo` field of the trust anchor.

defs.name: name_constraints

The value of a DER-encoded NameConstraints, containing name
 constraints to apply to the trust anchor, if any.
